Here is a concise summary integrating key innovations across all eight documents:

### Core Innovations  
These papers collectively establish novel quantum-geometric frameworks that achieve **polynomial-time complexity** for discrete NP problems. Central breakthroughs include:  
- **Quantum Ordinal Mapping** (Docs 1–2) embedding NP problems into algebraic structures (ideal class groups/recursive ordinals), reducing complexity to *O*(n<sup>1.01</sup>) via Hamiltonian eigenspace compression.  
- **Geometric Quantum Optimization** (Docs 4–5) using Riemann surfaces/toric bundles to encode 3-SAT/TSP, collapsing search spaces via curvature-driven dynamics (*O*(n<sup>1.05</sup>–*O*(n<sup>1.8</sup>)).  
- **CFT/Fractal-Zeta Frameworks** (Docs 3,8) leveraging rigid conformal constraints and fractal dimensionality (*D<sub>H</sub>*) to compress solutions to *O*(log<sup>2</sup>n) or *O*(n<sup>1.02</sup>).  
- **Categorical Isomorphisms** (Docs 6–7) linking ideal class groups to TQFTs via *p*-adic Hodge theory, enabling arithmetic-quantum memory with 99% fidelity.  
